{"aid": "40215276", "title": "Tuile \u2013 A Text User Interface Library for Zig", "url": "https://zig.news/akarpovskii/introducing-tuile-a-text-user-interface-library-for-zig-51ig", "domain": "zig.news", "votes": 1, "user": "jedisct1", "posted_at": "2024-04-30 19:34:53", "comments": 0, "source_title": "Introducing Tuile - a Text User Interface library for Zig", "source_text": "Introducing Tuile - a Text User Interface library for Zig - Zig NEWS\n\nSkip to content\n\nLog in Create account\n\n## Zig NEWS\n\nSoftware You Can Love Milan 2024 has been announced!\n\nCopied to Clipboard\n\nShare to Twitter Share to LinkedIn Share to Reddit Share to Hacker News Share\nto Facebook Share to Mastodon\n\nReport Abuse\n\nAndrei Karpovskii\n\nPosted on Apr 30\n\n1\n\n# Introducing Tuile - a Text User Interface library for Zig\n\n#showcase\n\nTuile is a Text User Interface library for Zig. It aims to be simple yet\npowerful enough to allow you to build rich user interfaces for your programs!\n\nFeatures:\n\n  * Declarative API\n  * Common widgets included\n  * Customizable themes\n  * Colors, text styles, and more\n\nLet\u2019s see an example:\n\n    \n    \n    const tuile = @import(\"tuile\"); pub fn stop(tui: ?*tuile.Tuile) void { tui.?.stop(); } pub fn main() !void { var tui = try tuile.Tuile.init(.{}); defer tui.deinit(); try tui.add( tuile.block( .{ .border = tuile.Border.all(), .border_type = .rounded, .layout = .{ .flex = 1 }, }, tuile.vertical(.{}, .{ tuile.label(.{ .text = \"Hello World!\" }), tuile.button(.{ .text = \"Quit\", .on_press = .{ .cb = @ptrCast(&stop), .payload = &tui, }, }), }), ), ); try tui.run(); }\n\n### Add it to your project\n\n  1. Add dependency to your build.zig.zon:\n\n    \n    \n    zig fetch --save https://github.com/akarpovskii/tuile/archive/refs/tags/v0.1.0.tar.gz\n\n  1. Import Tuile in build.zig and link ncurses:\n\n    \n    \n    const tuile = b.dependency(\"tuile\", .{}); exe.root_module.addImport(\"tuile\", tuile.module(\"tuile\")); exe.linkLibC(); exe.linkSystemLibrary(\"ncurses\");\n\nVisit Tuile's GitHub repository to explore examples and contribute to the\nlibrary.\n\n## Top comments (0)\n\nFor further actions, you may consider blocking this person and/or reporting\nabuse\n\n## Read next\n\n### Zig projects I'm working on...\n\nKarsten Schmidt - Sep 3 '22\n\n### Growing a {{mustache}} with Zig\n\nRafael Batiati - Aug 13 '22\n\n### Zig Visual Programming with Blockly\n\nLup Yuen Lee - Aug 8 '22\n\n### zbor - a CBOR en-/ decoder\n\nDavid Sugar - Jul 26 '22\n\nAndrei Karpovskii\n\n  * Joined\n\nApr 29, 2024\n\nOnce suspended, akarpovskii will not be able to comment or publish posts until\ntheir suspension is removed.\n\nOnce unsuspended, akarpovskii will be able to comment and publish posts again.\n\nOnce unpublished, all posts by akarpovskii will become hidden and only\naccessible to themselves.\n\nIf akarpovskii is not suspended, they can still re-publish their posts from\ntheir dashboard.\n\nOnce unpublished, this post will become invisible to the public and only\naccessible to Andrei Karpovskii.\n\nThey can still re-publish the post if they are not suspended.\n\nThanks for keeping Zig NEWS safe. Here is what you can do to flag akarpovskii:\n\nReport other inappropriate conduct\n\nUnflagging akarpovskii will restore default visibility to their posts.\n\nZig NEWS \u2014 Read the latest happenings in the global Zig community.\n\n  * Contact\n  * Home\n  * FAQs\n\n  * Code of Conduct\n  * ziggit.dev (forum)\n  * Privacy Policy\n  * Terms of Use\n  * ziglearn.org\n  * zigmonthly.org\n  * zigbin.io\n  * zig.show\n\nBuilt on Forem \u2014 the open source software that powers DEV and other inclusive\ncommunities.\n\nMade with love and Ruby on Rails. Zig NEWS \u00a9 2021 - 2024.\n\nTake off every Zig!\n\nLog in Create account\n\n", "frontpage": false}
